Kim Kardashian West has shared the first picture of herself with her niece Dream Kardashian. The 36-year-old reality star took to Instagram on Tuesday, March 7, to share an adorable snap of herself holding her three-month-old niece Dream, who is the daughter of Kim's younger brother Rob Kardashian and Blac Chyna. Kim simply captioned the snap: "Hey beautiful girl." Hey beautiful girl A post shared by Kim Kardashian West (@kimkardashian) on Mar 7, 2017 at 8:24am PST And Dream has been showered with love ever since she was born, with her father Rob, 29, recently taking to social media to gush about how he is the happiest he has "ever" been in his life when he is around the tiny tot, and he is sad he has to leave her because he will miss her "so much". Alongside a picture of the Arthur George sock designer with Dream, which was shared on his Instagram account, he wrote: "Saying bye to my beautiful baby girl ..... she is smiling at me. U see how she looking at her daddy I literally can't get enough of this girl,,, I never felt a love or happiness like this ever in my life and she makes me so happy ,,,about to miss her so much Love You baby Dream (sic)." PICS: Meet the new pregnant Beyonce Barbie And the 'Keeping Up With the Kardashians' star has touched the hearts of everyone, including his older sister Kourtney Kardashian. The 37-year-old television personality commented on post, and wrote: "That's beautiful Bobby (sic)." Rob's post came a few weeks after the reality star had reportedly moved out of his home with his 28-year-old partner. And it is believed the couple have gone their separate ways to allow Rob to focus on himself, his design work with his fashion label, and his baby. Speaking previously, a source said: "Rob is focusing more on himself, the baby and work. He's been focusing on his sock line more."  Bang Showbiz